.TH "MAP.GET" "3JS" "September 22, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Map.get \- Map.prototype.get()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]get()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]Map\f[R] instances
returns the value corresponding to the key in this \f[CR]Map\f[R], or
\f[CR]undefined\f[R] if there is none.
Object values are returned as the same reference that was originally
stored, not as a copy, so mutations to the returned object will be
reflected anywhere that reference is held, including inside the
\f[CR]Map\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] map = \f[B]new\f[R] Map();
map.set(\(dqbar\(dq, \(dqfoo\(dq);

console.log(map.get(\(dqbar\(dq));
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqfoo\(dq\f[R]

console.log(map.get(\(dqbaz\(dq));
\f[I]// Expected output: undefined\f[R]
.EE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
get(key)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]key\f[R]
The key of the value to return from the \f[CR]Map\f[R] object.
Object keys are compared by reference, not by value.
.SS Return value
The value associated with the specified key in the \f[CR]Map\f[R]
object.
If the key can\(cqt be found, \f[CR]undefined\f[R] is returned.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using get()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myMap = \f[B]new\f[R] Map();
myMap.set(\(dqbar\(dq, \(dqfoo\(dq);

console.log(myMap.get(\(dqbar\(dq)); \f[I]// Returns \(dqfoo\(dq\f[R]
console.log(myMap.get(\(dqbaz\(dq)); \f[I]// Returns undefined\f[R]
.EE
.SS Using get() to retrieve a reference to an object
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] arr = [];
\f[B]const\f[R] myMap = \f[B]new\f[R] Map();
myMap.set(\(dqbar\(dq, arr);

myMap.get(\(dqbar\(dq).push(\(dqfoo\(dq);

console.log(arr); \f[I]// [\(dqfoo\(dq]\f[R]
console.log(myMap.get(\(dqbar\(dq)); \f[I]// [\(dqfoo\(dq]\f[R]
.EE
